Greenlight Re




























Greenlight Re












		A.M. Best Ratings
	


			A-
		

			Greenlight Reinsurance, Ltd
		



			A-
		

			Greenlight Re Ireland, DAC
		



Strategy

CUSTOMER-CENTRIC APPROACH
to underwriting to develop long-term reinsurance relationships that deliver superior value to our partners in the best mutually beneficial market opportunities.
 
COLLABORATIVE RELATIONSHIPS
to support our partners in managing their business profitably. 
 
DIFFERENTIATED INVESTMENT APPROACH
to maximize book value per share. 
 
CONCENTRATE
our underwriting and investment portfolios on ideas in which we have the highest conviction.   
VISION

Greenlight Re strives to be the most responsive, client-focused reinsurer. We make our clients’ success our business.
BELIEF

Both our clients and brokers are our partners. Transparency, open communication and trust are paramount to achieving the best possible mutual outcome and maintaining strong, long-term partnerships. Our goals are best achieved through the long-term success of our partners.
BEHAVIOR

We treat our partners in a manner in which we want to be treated and are respectful of their views and objectives. We are collaborative and transparent, communicating openly and honestly with the highest levels of integrity. We work to resolve issues in an equitable way for all partners.
GOALS

DRIVE LONG-TERM BOOK VALUE GROWTH
through profitable underwriting and investing operations.
 
ALIGN THE INTERESTS
between all partners in a transaction and our shareholders.
 
BE TRANSPARENT AND RESPONSIVE
through a flat organizational structure with a small team of highly skilled underwriters that gives our partners access to decision makers.
 
EARN AN ECONOMIC PROFIT
on every reinsurance contract and every investment in all market conditions.
VALUES

A COLLABORATIVE WORKING STYLE
that will result in win-win solutions with our partners.
 
COMMITTED TO OUR EMPLOYEES
by providing training opportunities as well as a challenging and rewarding work environment.
 
COMMITTED TO OUR COMMUNITY
through supporting charitable organizations and encouraging community involvement.






				Our Team
			

						Executive Team
						








									
									Simon Burton
									

									
Chief Executive Officer

sburton@greenlightre.ky

D +1 345 749 0202
M +1 345 526 0202




Simon Burton joined Greenlight Re as Chief Executive Officer in July, 2017.  Previously, Simon served as Chief Executive Officer of S.A.C. Re, Ltd. from its inception until its sale to Hamilton Insurance Group, Ltd., where he was responsible, among other things, for building the company’s global reinsurance portfolio, which supported the material growth in book value.  Prior to SAC Re, Simon served in a variety of roles at Lancashire Group, including Deputy Chief Executive Officer and Chief Executive Officer of the company’s Bermuda subsidiary.  Simon also spent 10 years at Financial Solutions International, an underwriting division of ACE Limited, where he eventually rose to the role of President.  He received his Bachelor of Science degree in Mathematics from Imperial College, London University.








									
									Tim Courtis
									

									
Chief Financial Officer 

tim@greenlightre.ky

D +1 345 749 0205
M +1 345 525 9475




Tim Courtis has served as our Chief Financial Officer since May 2006.  Tim has over 20 years experience in the property and casualty reinsurance, captive and insurance industry.  Most recently Tim was President and Chief Financial Officer of European International Reinsurance Company Ltd., a subsidiary of Swiss Re, from August 1994 until April 2006, where he was responsible for the management and financial analysis of Swiss Re's Barbados based entities.  Prior to joining Swiss Re in 1994, Tim also worked for Continental Insurance in Barbados and International Risk Management Company in Bermuda where he performed duties as senior account manager to various captive insurance companies.  Tim is a Canadian Chartered Accountant and has a MBA from York University, Toronto and a Bachelor of Business from Wilfrid Laurier University, Waterloo.








									
									Brendan Barry
									

									
