Rena Strecker joined Greenlight Re in 2011 as a member of the finance and operations team and heads up middle office operations.   Rena has over 14 years’ experience in the reinsurance/insurance industry having held various positions in property & casualty insurance/reinsurance, life & pension and captive insurance.  Most recently Rena was consulting for AIG working in both London and New York with the capital management department and financial transformation project teams.  Prior to that Rena served as a Vice President at Goldman Sachs in London in the controllers department.  Rena is a Canadian Chartered Accountant, has a Bachelor of Business Administration from the University of Regina and an Associate in Reinsurance designation.











About us

Greenlight Capital Re, formed in 2004, is a Cayman Islands based publicly traded (ticker: GLRE) reinsurance holding company with two principal operating subsidiaries, Greenlight Reinsurance, Ltd., headquartered in the Cayman Islands and provides multi-line P&C reinsurance globally, and Greenlight Reinsurance Ireland, Ltd., based in Dublin, focuses on the European market.


								Cayman Islands Focus
								




Greenlight Reinsurance, Ltd. is based in the Cayman Islands and pursues reinsurance opportunities globally, with a focus on North America.  Consistent with our customer centric strategy, we look to develop long term relationships through an approach that will best add value to our brokers and clients.
 
We are, for the most part, business line and structure neutral, though our risk allocation will vary based on the perception of the opportunities available.  In segments where we have the strongest conviction, we prefer larger transactions in which we lead or take majority share.  For other segments, we look to partner with carriers who are view as best-in-class for their specific lines, usually starting with a small share with an eye to growing the relationship over time. 
The segments we are currently finding the most attractive in North America include pro-rata and low attachment excess transactions in medium to longer-tail lines.  The lines we recently have been most successful include:

Private Passenger Auto
Homeowner Quota-Share
Accident & Health,
Excess Casualty
Professional Liability
Niche Programs
Direct Investment



								Ireland Focus
								




Greenlight Reinsurance Ireland, Dedicated Activity Company. is based in Dublin and is focused on reinsurance opportunities in the London and Continental Europe markets.  We are, for the most part, business line and structure neutral, though our risk allocation will vary based on the perception of the opportunities available.  We look to partner with the larger, well-established syndicates and carriers who are viewed as best-in-class for specific lines. 
 
The segments as we are currently finding the most attractive in the London and European market include pro-rata and low attachment excess transactions in medium to longer-tail lines.  The lines and product structures we currently have the most interest include:

Specialty
Property Cat Retro
Multi-Line Aggregate Pillar
Risk Excess Covers
Quota-Share
Third Party Capital
Solvency II Capital Relief Products


