GLRE
Greenlight Capital Re Ltd

Greenlight Capital Re, Ltd. - Strategy, SWOT and Corporate Finance Report


                            Synopsis

Greenlight Capital Re, Ltd. - Strategy, SWOT and Corporate Finance Report, is a source of comprehensive company data and information. The report covers the company's structure, operation, SWOT analysis, product and service offerings and corporate actions, providing a 360˚ view of the company.

Summary

- Detailed information on Greenlight Capital Re, Ltd. required for business and competitor intelligence needs
- A study of the major internal and external factors affecting Greenlight Capital Re, Ltd. in the form of a SWOT analysis
- An in-depth view of the business model of Greenlight Capital Re, Ltd. including a breakdown and examination of key business segments
- Intelligence on Greenlight Capital Re, Ltd.'s mergers and acquisitions (MandA), strategic partnerships and alliances, capital raising, private equity transactions, and financial and legal advisors
- News about Greenlight Capital Re, Ltd., such as business expansion, restructuring, and contract wins
- Large number of easy-to-grasp charts and graphs that present important data and key trends

Reasons To Buy

- Gain understanding of  Greenlight Capital Re, Ltd. and the factors that influence its strategies.
- Track strategic initiatives of the company and latest corporate news and actions.
- Assess Greenlight Capital Re, Ltd. as a prospective partner, vendor or supplier.
- Support sales activities by understanding your customers' businesses better.
- Stay up to date on Greenlight Capital Re, Ltd.'s business structure, strategy and prospects.

Key Highlights

Greenlight Capital Re, Ltd. (Greenlight Capital Re) is a reinsurance company. The company offers a range of specialty property and casualty reinsurance products. Its casualty reinsurance products comprise general liability reinsurance, marine liability reinsurance, motor liability reinsurance and professional liability reinsurance. The company’s property reinsurance products include motor physical damage reinsurance, aviation reinsurance, energy reinsurance, commercial lines reinsurance and personal lines reinsurance. Its specialty reinsurance products comprise financial risk reinsurance, health reinsurance and workers’ compensation reinsurance. Greenlight Capital Re distributes its products principally through reinsurance brokers. The company has a presence in Cayman Islands, and Ireland. Greenlight Capital Re is headquartered in Grand Cayman, the Cayman Islands.

The company reported gross premiums written of US$502.1 million for the fiscal year ended December 2015 (FY2015), representing a decline of 54.9% over its previous year. Its net premium written was US$408.4 million in FY2015, representing a decline of 15.3% over its previous year.

                            













